context: In December 2005, activist <a0_0><b4_0>Suzanne Shell<b4_0/><a0_0/> filed suit demanding Internet Archive pay her US $100,000 for archiving her web site <a1_0><b5_0>profane-justice.org<b5_0/><a1_0/> between 1999 and 2004. Internet Archive filed a declaratory judgment action in the United States District Court for the <a2_0><b6_0>Northern District of California<b6_0/><a2_0/> on <b8_0>January 20, 2006<b8_0/>, seeking a judicial determination that Internet Archive did not violate Shell's copyright. Shell responded and brought a countersuit against Internet Archive for archiving her site, which she alleges is in violation of her terms of service. On February 13, 2007, a judge for the United States District Court for the <a3_0><b7_0>District of Colorado<b7_0/><a3_0/> dismissed all counterclaims except breach of contract. The Internet Archive did not move to dismiss copyright infringement claims Shell asserted arising out of its copying activities, which would also go forward.
